726997f-a.text:
Jamaica Ave., north side, opposite 75th Street (formerly Eads Ave.), showing Denter Park Hotel; which is east of the Truants Home that stands on the site of the former J. I. Snediker hotel.  Owners of the Denter Park Hotel were H. Woodruff, 1860; J. Hillegar, 1891; one Lypack, 1896; and also one Hasenflug.  Hiram Woodruff's first roadhouse was on Stony Road at the north side of Jamaica Ave., where Jewish Cemetery is now.  This is a set of three views.  View
No. 2 also shows the Murphy house on the right.

1922.

Views 2 & 3: April 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

726998f-a.text:
Jamaica Ave., north side, between 75th and 76th Streets, showing in a set of three views showing Murphy's house and blacksmith shop, which was established in 1835.  It was here that many a famous horse, running on the Union Course Race Track was shod.

1922.

Views 2 & 3: April 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
